This paper is primarily focused on provenance for database queries, which falls under the category of databases (cs.DB). The paper also introduces a tracing model for Nested Relational Calculus, which is a programming language for working with relational databases, and defines trace slicing algorithms, which are techniques used in programming languages (cs.PL). The paper also discusses the importance of reproducibility, which is a concern in software engineering (cs.SE), and the use of provenance for increasing understanding, which is relevant to artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper presents formal definitions and correctness properties, which are related to logic (cs.LO).
